A pizza restaurant is offering a special price on pizzas with $2$ toppings. They offer the toppings below:

$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|}
\hline \text{Pepperoni} & \text{Sausage} & \text{Ham}
\\ \hline
\text{Chicken} & \text{Green pepper} & \text{Onion}
\\ \hline
\text{Mushroom} & \text{Pineapple}
\\ \hline
\end{array}$

Suppose that Rosa's favorite is sausage and onion, but her mom can't remember that, and she is going to randomly choose $2$ different toppings.

**What is the probability that Rosa's mom chooses sausage and onion?**

[[☃ radio 1]]

Sofie claims to be a tasting expert. To test her abilities, someone bakes Sofie a cake using $3$ of the following ingredients:

$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|}
\hline \text{Coffee} & \text{Vanilla} & \text{Sea salt}
\\ \hline
\text{Nutmeg} & \text{Cinnamon} & \text{Ginger}
\\ \hline
\end{array}$

Sofie's challenge is to identify which set of $3$ ingredients was used in the cake. Suppose that Sofie is just randomly guessing.

**What is the probability that Sofie correctly identifies the set of $3$ ingredients in the cake?**

